postcontent: Selling my Smith & Wesson model 586-1, 357 Mag (6 shot) revolver. This was also known as the "Distinguished Combat Magnum" and is an L-frame with 4" barrel. Has adjustable rear sight and red ramp front sight. The target grips aren't a factory set but are custom and look similar and have a very unique two-toned wood grain. The 586 was one of the finest revolvers ever made. In the 80s it was the main competitor to the Colt Python and you just don't see them like this anymore. Bluing is absolutely beautiful. Trigger is smooth and breaks like glass. I have the original box and paperwork. Everything locks up tight and functions as it should. I hate to let it go… only reason I'm selling is because I've been hit with some financial burden. Dropped price today (09/28/16) to $650 which is a great deal.
